Washburn County Health Department is sharing a COVID-19 Update.
August 28 at 5:19 PM ·

In order to keep our kids in school, we need everyone to work together to prevent the spread of COVID-19 in schools so that they can safely stay open. Here is a screening tool for parents to use BEFORE sending their kids to school each day. If your child meets the criteria in the screening tool, please keep them home. If your child is ill, discuss with their primary care provider if they should be tested for COVID-19. Be sure to follow the policies of your child's school district.
Link to PDF version: https://www.co.washburn.wi.us/images/custom/COVID-19%20screening%20checklist%20-%20schools.pdf

shared_text:
The River - A Wesleyan Church
August 4 at 8:10 PM ·

School is just around the corner and our Women's Ministry is looking out for those kiddos in a special way. On Thursday, August 13 from 4-7 pm, we have two volunteer hair stylists who are graciously offering FREE haircuts to school aged kids. You do NOT have to attend The River to sign your child up.

Please contact us through Facebook Messenger or call/text 715-296-7881 to sign up for a 20 minute haircut.
There are limited spots available!

Maybe school is starting back and you are a little stressed or worried about other aspects of the school year? School shoes? Supplies? New glasses? Send us a message and we would love to have a discreet conversation with your family about your needs.

post_text: The Northwood School District held the second planning meeting yesterday and would like to thank all those that completed the survey that was recently sent out. The response was great. Responses of the survey were reviewed as we kicked off the collaboration. This feedback assisted in the progress towards the planning for the 2020-21 school year. The goal is to have a list of proactive health and wellness measures in place and a draft of our plan for returning to school which will be presented at the next Board meeting on July 16th. If you didn’t get a chance, please use this link to complete the survey. https://forms.gle/9Fq7mc1UdQgUaTwUA

post_text: This fall we will reopen school and education will resume in some capacity. Our goal is to determine how we can reopen the Northwood School District while keeping the health and safety of our students and staff a top priority. Use this link https://forms.gle/9Fq7mc1UdQgUaTwUA and take a few moments to complete the Back to School Survey in order for the Planning Committee to best meet the needs of our students and community as plans are solidified to return to school on August 20th. We appreciate your feedback!

Hello Northwood Families, Today, the Wisconsin Department of Public Instruction (DPI) released their Education Forward: Safely and Successfully Reopening Wisconsin Schools guidance document. The Northwood School District will be looking at these guidelines very closely. There is also a small group of parents, community members, and school employees from different areas of the building (Administration, Teachers, Food Service, Safety Coordinators, School Board Member, etc.) that are working on a responsive plan for reopening our school for next school year.
https://dpi.wi.gov/sspw/2019-novel-coronavirus

The Richard I. Bong Veterans Historical Center sponsors an annual high school essay contest. This year's prompt honored fifty years of Earth Day. Mrs. Duffy passed this challenge to the Advanced English class with success!

Special congratulations go to the Grand Prize Winner, Abby Michie!

A round of applause goes to the Second Runner-up, Collin Krmpotich!

Elbow bumps and big smiles to the Honorable Mentions, Kayla Schultz and Georgia Becherer.

post_text: The Northwood School District is proud to join other districts throughout the state during the "Fields of Light" event. Tonight at 8:20 pm (20:20 military time) to 8:40 pm, we will turn on the lights at the Liautaud Field in recognition of the class of 2020. We invite students, families, and community members to drive by to see the lights and make some noise! Please do not use this event as a social gathering but rather a demonstration of how proud we are of our Northwood class of 2020. Thank you for the continued support of our district and the class of 2020 as they continue to miss many senior year events during this school closure. Keep the Evergreen Hope alive!

post_text:
Northwood High School is excited to announce that our School Board has decided to partner with WITC for our Driver’s Education program beginning the 2020-21 school year. This partnership will provide our students with more flexibility for the classroom component of the course. There will be three options with this change to the classroom aspect:
Online Option - Learn online at your own pace.
Interactive Video (ITV) Option - Learn during classes in the evening that connect with a live instructor.
Face-To-Face Option - This face-to-face option will be taught at Northwood School either before school, after school, or classes during the summer.
Regarding the behind the wheel time training, this will still be done at the Northwood School District through WITC. The same driving instructors plan to continue their roles as usual.
If you have any questions, you can email Mr. Kelly or Mrs. Farris at the Northwood School or contact the WITC Driver Training Program at 1-800-243-9482 ext 5777 or driversed@witc.edu

post_text: NEW DISTRICT HOURS: Hey Northwood Families. We hope everyone is doing well and prepared for the Safer at Home Order that goes into effect tomorrow morning. Due to this new emergency order, the school building will only be open Monday, Wednesday, and Friday from 7 am to 2 pm for essential staff to prepare and deliver meals to families, preserve the school building, and continue finance functions that may need to be done on-site. Please call us during these hours if you have any questions. We wish you well.

post_text:
Northwood families and community members,
There are many unknowns as this time, which can make it difficult for children and adolescents (and even adults) to fully process what is happening across the country and throughout the world. Linked below is some information that might be helpful if you have children at home feeling anxiety or stress around COVID-19 and the impact it is having on our "normal" routines. We are in this together! Stay well!

* If you have a mental health crisis, I urge you to utilize the Washburn County Mental Health Crisis Line @ 1-888-860-0373 or the Douglas County Mental Health Crisis Line @ 715-392-8216, which are both available 24/7/365

*The SAMHSA Disaster Distress Helpline also provides 24/7/365 crisis counseling and support for people experiencing emotional distress related to any natural or human-caused disaster. Call 1-800-985-5990 or text TalkWithUs to 66746 to be connected with a trained crisis counselor.

*We will have other resources on our District webpage soon.

Important Message: On Friday, March 13, 2020, Governor Tony Evers issued a statewide closure of all public and private schools for pupil instruction and extracurricular activities as part of the state’s efforts to respond to and contain the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19) in Wisconsin. Northwood School will be in session Monday and Tuesday, March 16 & 17. The mandated closure of schools will begin on Wednesday, March 18, with an anticipated reopening on April 6.
The School District is committed to doing what’s in the best interest of our students and community and want everyone to be assured we are working diligently to create a plan to meet student needs during the closure.

post_text:
Our neighbors at the Birchwood School showing support to our Northwood family....

"The HS Student Council, with the help of the Birchwood and Mellen communities, raised $1,700 to be presented to the Northwood School District. The money was raised for a scholarship fund set up for Paul Vaara.

Mr. Vaara was the 5th grade Northwood teacher and softball coach who died suddenly and leaves behind two school-aged daughters. Mr. Senn presented the check to the Northwood Athletic Director, Curt Zamzow, today. The community of Birchwood truly is amazing. #wearebirchwood"

Our annual Family & Community Night at Northwood is on Thursday, March 19th from 4:00 - 7:30 p.m. This event is a fantastic opportunity for families and community members to come together to celebrate student achievement and learn about activities and resources throughout our community. There will be a variety of activities happening throughout the school on this evening.
*PK-12 Student-led conferences
*School and Community table displays in the gymnasium
*FAB Lab Open House
*Northwood Education Foundation Dinner (donation)
*Book Fair
If you would like to join us and share information with a display table on Family & Community Night, please reserve a table by Tuesday, March 17th. Email Mrs. Denninger (tammie_denninger@northwoodk12wi.com ) or call the school office at (715) 466-2297.

post_text:
What a Great Elementary Music Winter Concert last night! Thanks to all for your hard work to make the concert a success. The Family and Consumer Sciences, Music, Art, and Spanish, departments worked together to create the theme: “Christmas Around the World.” About 10-12 countries from around the world were represented through music, art, foods, cultures, and other traditions.
The Spanish class students hosted the refreshments and treats after the concert. Students, parents and our community had the opportunity to have a taste of Christmas around the world.

Over the past few days, we have accumulated much snow throughout the state including our district. This message is a reminder to families that for safety, our buses will only run on plowed roads tomorrow morning. Please travel safely and stay warm. Winter is here!

post_text:
Annual Back to School Picnic
August 20, 2019
5:30 - 7:00

Families can meet the staff, tour the building, and check out the classrooms prior to the first day of school.

Hot dogs and chips will be served all evening. Informational tables will be set up throughout the commons. Our young Evergreens can enjoy the bounce house and the playground.

Informational meetings are also planned during the picnic:
5:30 - 6:00 5th-8th grade Flag Football meeting & sign up - library

post_text:
The 2018-2019 High Quiz Bowl season ended with jubilation as the Northwood Evergreen team battled to the championship title at the CESA #12 tournament on Wednesday. Knowledge was tested and wits were matched question for question, with the audience on the edge of our seats. Ultimately the Mighty Evergreens kept calm, answered wisely, pulled ahead, and took home the First Place Trophy.

Please congratulate Jade, Haakon, Margaret, and Lucas for this great accomplishment, the first time Northwood has taken the first place tourney trophy.

It was awesome to watch.

Game One: Beat Drummond 65-40
Game Two: Beat Phillips 85-35
Game Three: Beat South Shore 80-50
Game Four: Beat Ashland 60-55
Game Five: Defeated by Ashland 45-50
But it is a double-elimination tournament so we played them again...
FINAL GAME: Beat Ashland 45-30

post_text: Congratulations to the Northwood High School forensics team, who performed at this weekend's state tournament. They joined 4100 students from 340 schools around Wisconsin to bring their best speaking voices to one round of competition. Our students were entered in the categories of group interpretation, play acting, informative speaking, prose speaking, and poetry reading. Overall we were awarded five bronze medals, 10 silver medals, and 4 gold medals. Northwood forensicators are loud and proud!
